IN	6 slices bacon
IN	1 bunch collard greens, rinsed and trimmed
IN	1/3 cup vinegar
IN	salt to taste
IN	ground black pepper to taste
IN	ground cayenne pepper to taste
PR	Place bacon in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium high heat until evenly brown.
PR	Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add collard greens, bacon (with grease), vinegar, salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper.
PR	Boil until greens are tender, about 30 minutes.
